'''Endrick Felipe Moreira de Sousa Pessoa''' (born 21 July 2006), known as '''Endrick''' ({{IPA|pt-BR|ˈẽ(j̃)dɾik(i)|lang}}),<ref>{{cite web |author=Forvo Team |title=Endrick pronunciation: How to pronounce Endrick in Portuguese |url=https://forvo.com/word/endrick/ |website=Forvo.com}}</ref> is a Brazilian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]], on loan from [[La Liga]] club [[Real Madrid]], and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

==Early life==
Endrick was born in Taguatinga, Federal District, and has one brother and two sisters.<ref>{{cite web |title=Endrick: My dream is to play in Europe, but I'm focused on Palmeiras |url=https://www.laprensalatina.com/endrick-my-dream-is-to-play-in-europe-but-im-focused-on-palmeiras/ |website=La Prensa Latina Media |access-date=14 December 2023 |date=9 November 2022 |archive-date=30 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130113158/https://www.laprensalatina.com/endrick-my-dream-is-to-play-in-europe-but-im-focused-on-palmeiras/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="theguardian0">{{cite web |last1=Rabelo |first1=Thiago |title=Endrick: 'People say I have a heart of ice and I'm very cold with decisions' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/dec/10/endrick-i-have-fun-playing-football-thats-what-i-want-to-do-in-my-life |website=The Guardian |publisher=The Observer |access-date=14 December 2023 |date=10 December 2023}}</ref> His father, Douglas de Sousa Silva Ramos, pursued a career in professional football and left his family when Endrick was eleven years old to play for several small clubs in [[Brasília]].<ref name="theguardian0"/> His mother was unemployed and homeless during that time, forcing Endrick and his siblings to reside in an orphanage in [[São Paulo]] until his father returned after six months.<ref name="theguardian0"/> Both his parents worked at a cafe on the city's underground train station before his father received employment by Palmeiras as a janitor.<ref name="bbc"/><ref name="theatheltic"/>

Endrick started playing football at the age of four,<ref name="hitc">{{cite news |date=15 December 2022 |title=Club officially announce they have sold £62m Arsenal & Liverpool target to European giants |url=http://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2022/12/15/club-officially-announce-they-have-sold-62m-arsenal-liverpool-target-to-european-giants/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221217164443/https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2022/12/15/club-officially-announce-they-have-sold-62m-arsenal-liverpool-target-to-european-giants/ |archive-date=17 December 2022 |access-date=15 December 2022 |website=HITC}}</ref> and his father published his goals on [[YouTube]] to attract interested parties among the big Brazilian clubs.<ref name="clarin">{{cite web |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/endrick-felipe-delantero-brasileno-15-anos-fascina-fifa_0_7bkI0D4G24.html |title=Quién es Endrick Felipe, el delantero brasileño de 12 años que fascina a la FIFA |website=[[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín]] |date=21 January 2022 |language=es |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=11 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221011222854/https://www.clarin.com/deportes/endrick-felipe-delantero-brasileno-15-anos-fascina-fifa_0_7bkI0D4G24.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Endrick vowed to become a professional footballer to help his family after his parents were unable to feed him.<ref name="bbc">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/60246750|title=Endrick: Brazilian, 15, matching Neymar and attracting attention from Europe's leading clubs|publisher=BBC Sport|date=8 February 2022|access-date=8 February 2022|archive-date=25 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221025155002/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/60246750|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="theatheltic">{{cite web |last1=Cortegana |first1=Mario |title=Inside the deal that saw Real Madrid win the race for Endrick, the Brazilian wonderkid |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4066362/2023/01/09/endrick-real-madrid/ |website=The Athletic |access-date=8 December 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230403153520/https://theathletic.com/4066362/2023/01/09/endrick-real-madrid/ |archive-date=3 April 2023 |language=en |url-status=live |date=9 January 2023}}</ref> At the age of eight, he trained in a [[Real Madrid]] camp with his friends at [[Águas Claras, Federal District|Águas Claras]]; he grew up supporting Real Madrid and idolised [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].<ref name="marca0">{{cite web |last1=Félix Díaz |first1=José |title=Endrick: My parents wanted to name me Di Stefano |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2023/07/07/64a7eb4722601d03318b45a5.html |website=MARCA |access-date=14 December 2023 |language=en |date=7 July 2023 |archive-date=14 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230714215107/https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2023/07/07/64a7eb4722601d03318b45a5.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He was also inspired by other Brazilians who played for Madrid such as [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], [[Vinícius Jr.]], [[Rodrygo]] and [[Éder Militão]].<ref name="marca0"/>

==Club career==
===Palmeiras===
After nearly signing for [[São Paulo FC|São Paulo]], Endrick joined the [[Palmeiras]] youth team at the age of 11.<ref name="bbc"/> In the next five years, he would score 165 goals in 169 games for Palmeiras youth teams.<ref name="clarin"/> Endrick participated in the 2022 [[Copa São Paulo de Futebol Júnior]], where he scored eight goals in seven matches and was voted Player of the Tournament by supporters, after leading Palmeiras to their first title.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/artigo/_/id/9799805/franceses-juntam-real-madrid-ingleses-observar-joia-palmeiras-por-que-assedio-nao-preocupa-clube-paulista |title=Franceses se juntam a Real Madrid e ingleses para observar joia do Palmeiras; veja por que assédio não preocupa clube paulista |website=[[ESPN (Brazil)|ESPN]] |date=18 January 2022 |language=pt-br |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=10 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221010023108/https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/artigo/_/id/9799805/franceses-juntam-real-madrid-ingleses-observar-joia-palmeiras-por-que-assedio-nao-preocupa-clube-paulista |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/endrick-brazil-45m-wonderkid-european-giants-fighting/blt1360445d774946a8 |first=Tauan |last=Ambrósio |title=Endrick: Brazil's new €45m wonderkid has European giants fighting over him |website=[[Goal.com]] |date=28 January 2022 |access-date=31 January 2022 |archive-date=14 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221214234111/https://www.goal.com/en/news/endrick-brazil-45m-wonderkid-european-giants-fighting/blt1360445d774946a8 |url-status=live }}</ref> Following the tournament, he caught the attention of international media and several major European clubs.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-erling-haaland-endrick-22827048 |title=Man City dealt Erling Haaland 'blow' as Gary Lineker hails 'special' Brazilian teenage sensation |work=[[Manchester Evening News]] |date=21 January 2022 |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=8 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221008161330/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-erling-haaland-endrick-22827048 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2022/01/13/fc-barcelona-want-to-sign-15-year-old-brazilian-wonderkid/?sh=72a5517b3a04 |title=FC Barcelona Want To Sign 15-Year-Old Brazilian Wonderkid |work=[[Forbes]] |date=13 January 2022 |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=6 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006233335/https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2022/01/13/fc-barcelona-want-to-sign-15-year-old-brazilian-wonderkid/?sh=72a5517b3a04 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sport.es/en/news/barca/barca-to-step-up-scouting-of-endrick-as-palmeiras-eye-semifinal-13117172 |title=Barça to step up scouting of Endrick as Palmeiras eye semifinal |website=[[Sport.es]] |date=19 January 2022 |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=10 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221010045754/https://www.sport.es/en/news/barca/barca-to-step-up-scouting-of-endrick-as-palmeiras-eye-semifinal-13117172 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Endrick made his senior professional debut on 6 October 2022, coming on as a second-half substitute in Palmeiras' 4–0 league win over Coritiba.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ge.globo.com/sp/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/06-10-2022/palmeiras-coritiba.ghtml |title=Contagem regressiva! Palmeiras goleia Coritiba e abre 12 pontos na liderança |website=Globo |date=6 October 2023 |language=pt-br |access-date=7 October 2022 |archive-date=28 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128225706/https://ge.globo.com/sp/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/06-10-2022/palmeiras-coritiba.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> At the age of 16 years, two months and 16 days, he became the youngest player to appear for the Palmeiras first team.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/ultimas-noticias/enm/2022/10/07/endrick-se-torna-o-atleta-mais-jovem-a-jogar-pelo-palmeiras-na-historia.htm |title=Endrick se torna o atleta mais jovem a jogar pelo Palmeiras na história |website=UOL |date=6 October 2022 |language=pt-br |access-date=8 October 2022 |archive-date=8 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221008104055/https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/ultimas-noticias/enm/2022/10/07/endrick-se-torna-o-atleta-mais-jovem-a-jogar-pelo-palmeiras-na-historia.htm |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first two goals on 25 October, in a 3–1 win over [[Athletico Paranaense]], becoming the second youngest goalscorer in the history of Brazil's Série A.<ref>{{cite news |title=Endrick se torna segundo mais jovem a marcar na história do Campeonato Brasileiro; veja top-10 |url=https://oglobo.globo.com/tudo-sobre/esporte/noticia/2022/10/endrick-se-torna-segundo-mais-jovem-a-marcar-na-historia-do-campeonato-brasileiro-veja-top-10.ghtml |access-date=27 October 2022 |website=Globo |language=pt-br |archive-date=27 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221027101756/https://oglobo.globo.com/tudo-sobre/esporte/noticia/2022/10/endrick-se-torna-segundo-mais-jovem-a-marcar-na-historia-do-campeonato-brasileiro-veja-top-10.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> Endrick then achieved his first trophy with the first team, winning the league with three games in hand following a 4–0 home win over [[Fortaleza Esporte Clube|Fortaleza]] on 2 November. He scored his third goal in seven appearances during the match as Palmeiras secured an eleventh league title in club history.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Savarese |first1=Mauricio |title=Endrick scores as Palmeiras wins 11th Brazilian soccer title |url=https://news.yahoo.com/endrick-scores-palmeiras-wins-11th-031939138.html |website=Yahoo News |access-date=19 October 2023 |date=3 November 2022 |archive-date=30 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030012254/https://news.yahoo.com/endrick-scores-palmeiras-wins-11th-031939138.html |url-status=live }}</ref> At the end of the season, Endrick was voted the most promising player in the Série A.<ref>{{cite news |title=A closer look at Endrick |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/12/15/a-closer-look-at-endrick |publisher=[[Real Madrid CF]] |access-date=19 October 2023 |date=15 December 2022 |archive-date=30 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030012253/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/12/15/a-closer-look-at-endrick |url-status=live }}</ref>

[[File:Endrick-Palmeiras-Liverpool-abr24-2.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Endrick playing for [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] in 2024]]

On 11 October 2023, Endrick was named by English newspaper ''[[The Guardian]]'' as one of the best talents born in 2006 worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/oct/11/next-generation-2023-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football|title=Next Generation 2023: 60 of the best young talents in world football|first1=Marcus|last1=Christenson|first2=Steven|last2=Bloor|first3=Garry|last3=Blight|date=11 October 2023|access-date=11 October 2023|work=The Guardian|archive-date=12 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231012014039/https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/oct/11/next-generation-2023-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football|url-status=live}}</ref> After experiencing an extensive goal-drought throughout the season,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tavero |first1=Fernando S. |title=Endrick se atasca |url=https://as.com/futbol/internacional/endrick-se-atasca-n/ |website=Diario AS |access-date=8 December 2023 |language=es |date=25 March 2023 |archive-date=8 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208063403/https://as.com/futbol/internacional/endrick-se-atasca-n/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Endrick scored two goals and added an assist on 1 November in a 3-4 [[Comeback (sports)|comeback]] win against [[Botafogo de Futebol e Regatas|Botafogo]] at the [[Estádio Olímpico Nilton Santos]]. The game was 3-0 at the end of the first half. Endrick scored early in the second half and was shown on screen telling his teammates "just pass me the ball", a phrase he'd later apologize for. With the win, Palmeiras moved three points behind Botafogo, who were then first in the table.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/watch-endrick-real-madrid-striker-skill-palmeiras-comeback-botafogo/bltd94531d1e6b0fbce|title=WATCH: Stop that, Endrick! Real Madrid-bound striker scores beauty after outrageous fake shot skill as Palmeiras complete crazy comeback against Botafogo|website=[[Goal.com]]|first=Peter|last=McVitie|date=2 November 2023|access-date=3 November 2023|archive-date=3 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231103202917/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/watch-endrick-real-madrid-striker-skill-palmeiras-comeback-botafogo/bltd94531d1e6b0fbce|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2023/11/01/botafogo-x-palmeiras---campeonato-brasileiro.htm|title=Botafogo abre 3 a 0, Palmeiras vira nos acréscimos e incendeia o Brasileiro|work=Universo Online|first=Gabriela|last=Brino|date=1 November 2023|access-date=3 November 2023|language=pt-br|archive-date=3 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231103015350/https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2023/11/01/botafogo-x-palmeiras---campeonato-brasileiro.htm|url-status=live}}</ref> Palmeiras won their second consecutive league title, after Endrick scored a goal in a 1–1 draw to [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]] on 6 December, two points above second-place [[Grêmio]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vickery |first1=Tim |title=Endrick stars as Palmeiras claim extraordinary Brazilian title |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/39060719/endrick-stars-palmeiras-claim-extraordinary-brazilian-title |website=ESPN |access-date=7 December 2023 |language=en |date=7 December 2023 |archive-date=8 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208031719/https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/39060719/endrick-stars-palmeiras-claim-extraordinary-brazilian-title |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Mukherjee |first1=Soham |title=WATCH: Endrick hits the Griddy! Real Madrid-bound superstar pulls out iconic celebration after scoring another vital goal as Palmeiras win Brazilian league title for 12th time |url=https://www.goal.com/en-au/lists/endrick-griddy-real-madrid-palmeiras-win-brazilian-league-title-12th-time/blt8b45c870bda2e402#cs2a3b26471e86e9dc |website=Goal |access-date=7 December 2023 |language=en |date=7 December 2023 |archive-date=7 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231207213413/https://www.goal.com/en-au/lists/endrick-griddy-real-madrid-palmeiras-win-brazilian-league-title-12th-time/blt8b45c870bda2e402#cs2a3b26471e86e9dc |url-status=live }}</ref> He finished the season with eleven goals, the second highest scored in a Serie A season by an under-18 player behind [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mahanty |first1=Sourav |title=Real Madrid signing Endrick breaks Neymar's record |url=https://therealchamps.com/posts/real-madrid-signing-endrick-neymar-record |website=The Real Champs |access-date=7 December 2023 |date=7 December 2023 |archive-date=7 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231207213414/https://therealchamps.com/posts/real-madrid-signing-endrick-neymar-record |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 16 May 2024, Endrick was forced to leave the field on a stretcher due to an apparent right leg injury during Palmeiras' clash against [[Independiente del Valle]] in a [[2024 Copa Libertadores group stage|Copa Libertadores group stage]] match, and he was subject to further medical tests.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Cortegana |first=Mario |date=2024-05-16 |title=Endrick to undergo tests after leaving Palmeiras game on stretcher |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5498296/2024/05/16/endrick-injury-copa-america-brazil/ |access-date=2024-05-16 |work=[[The New York Times]] |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=16 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240516124909/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5498296/2024/05/16/endrick-injury-copa-america-brazil/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
On 15 December 2022, [[La Liga]] club [[Real Madrid]] announced that they had reached an agreement with Palmeiras, Endrick, and his family to sign him in July 2024, when he turned 18.<ref>{{cite news |date=15 December 2022 |title=Official Announcement: Endrick |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/club/announcements/official-announcement-endrick |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221216061517/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/12/15/official-announcement-endrick |archive-date=16 December 2022 |access-date=15 December 2022 |publisher=[[Real Madrid CF]]}}</ref> The official signing fee was undisclosed by the clubs, but was reported as an extendable three-year deal for a fixed amount of €60 million plus €12 million in taxes.<ref>{{cite news|last=De La Fuente|first=Homero|url=https://www.cnn.com/2022/12/15/football/real-madrid-endrick-palmeiras-spt-intl/index.html|title=Real Madrid signs 16-year-old Brazilian striker Endrick from Palmeiras for reported $63.6 million fee|publisher=[[CNN]] |date=15 December 2022|access-date=15 December 2022|archive-date=15 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221215183009/https://www.cnn.com/2022/12/15/football/real-madrid-endrick-palmeiras-spt-intl/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref> However, some other sources reported the fee was fixed at €35 million, with the remaining €25 million subject to achieving specific sporting objectives.<ref>{{cite news|last=Ruiz|first=Marco|url=https://en.as.com/soccer/endrick-to-join-real-madrid-for-35-million-n/|title=Endrick to join Real Madrid for €35 million|publisher=[[Diario AS]] |date=12 December 2022|access-date=15 December 2022|archive-date=15 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221215093748/https://en.as.com/soccer/endrick-to-join-real-madrid-for-35-million-n/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 July 2024, Real Madrid confirmed that Endrick would sign a six-year deal.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Official Announcement: Endrick's unveiling |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/club/announcements/comunicado-oficial-presentacion-de-endrick-19-07-2024|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=19 July 2024 |access-date=25 July 2024|archive-date=25 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725153034/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/club/announcements/comunicado-oficial-presentacion-de-endrick-19-07-2024|url-status=live}}</ref> He was unveiled as a new player on 27 July at the [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 July 2024 |title=Tearful Endrick unveiled as Real Madrid player |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/video/12606/13185788/tearful-endrick-unveiled-as-real-madrid-player |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=[[Sky Sports]]}}</ref>

On 25 August, Endrick made his debut in a 3–0 home win against [[Real Valladolid]] in La Liga, scoring the third goal after his introduction as a substitute in the 86th-minute.<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 August 2024 |title=Victoria en el regreso al Bernabéu |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/es-ES/noticias/futbol/primer-equipo/cronicas/cronica-rm-valladolid-j2-liga-25-08-2024 |access-date=25 August 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF (in Spanish)}}</ref> He also became the youngest foreigner to score for the club in La Liga's history (aged 18 years and 35 days) surpassing [[Raphaël Varane]], who scored against [[Rayo Vallecano]] aged 18 years and 152 days.<ref>{{cite web|date=26 August 2024 |publisher=ge |title=Endrick atinge marca com gol relâmpago em estreia no Real Madrid |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-espanhol/noticia/2024/08/26/endrick-atinge-marca-com-gol-relampago-em-estreia-no-real-madrid.ghtml}}<!-- auto-translated from Portuguese by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> On 17 September, Endrick scored on his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut when he scored the final goal in 3–1 win against [[VfB Stuttgart]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|league phase]], becoming the youngest player to score for Real Madrid in the competition and also becoming the youngest Brazilian footballer to score in the competition, aged 18 years and 58 days.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-17 |title=Endrick Scores Goal in Real Madrid Champions League Debut |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/endrick-goal-real-madrid-champions-league-debut |access-date=2024-09-18 |publisher=[[Sports Illustrated]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-17 |title=Brazil teenager Endrick becomes Real Madrid's youngest Champions League scorer |url=https://apnews.com/article/endrick-real-madrid-champions-league-289b765445cf98cfc63c868a80a925f5 |access-date=2024-09-18 |publisher=[[AP News]]}}</ref> On 2 April, Endrick became the first player since [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] in the [[2012–13 Real Madrid CF season|2012–13]] season to score five goals in a single [[Copa del Rey]] campaign for Real Madrid, later finishing as the tournament's joint second top scorer. He opened the scoring in the semi-final first leg against [[Real Sociedad]] and added his fifth with a trademark chipped finish in the return leg, helping Madrid reach the [[2025 Copa del Rey final|final]].<ref>{{cite web|date=2 April 2025|title=Endrick Will Challenge Cristiano Ronaldo in the Copa del Rey Final with Real Madrid|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/copa-del-rey/articles-video/endrick-will-challenge-cristiano-ronaldo-in-the-copa-del-rey-final-with-real-madrid-2025-04-02|publisher=beIN Sports|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

On 21 May, Real Madrid’s medical services diagnosed Endrick with a right hamstring-tendon injury that would keep him out for at least two months, ruling him out of the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|date=21 May 2025|title=Endrick unlikely to feature at Club World Cup with hamstring injury|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles/endrick-unlikely-to-feature-at-club-world-cup-with-hamstring-injury-2025-05-21|publisher=beIN Sports|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref> In August 2025, he acquired the number 9 shirt ahead of the 2025–26 season, his new number being vacated by [[Kylian Mbappé]] changing to the number 10.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles/end-of-the-debate-endrick-to-wear-no-9-at-real-madrid-gonzalo-garc%C3%ADa-takes-no-16-2025-08-08 |title=End of the Debate! Endrick to Wear No. 9 at Real Madrid, Gonzalo García Takes No. 16 |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=8 August 2025 }}</ref> On 1 November 2025, he made his first appearance under new manager [[Xabi Alonso]], in a 4–0 win against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6700460/2025/10/10/endrick-real-madrid-analysis/|title=Real Madrid's Endrick has not played in five months. What's going on?|first=Mario|last=Cortegana|date=10 October 2025|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribuna.com/en/blogs/endrick-finally-makes-first-apperance-under-xabi-alonso-at-r/|title=Endrick finally makes first apperance [sic] under Xabi Alonso at Real Madrid in Valencia clash - shares sweet moments with Vini Jr and Mbappe|first=Olga|last=Melnikova|date=1 November 2025|website=Tribuna.com}}</ref>

====Loan to Lyon====
On 23 December 2025, Endrick joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] on a six-month loan deal. Lyon paid a loan fee of €1 million plus half of his wages.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/arrivee-d-endrick-a-l-ol-jusqu-a-la-fin-de-la-saison|title=Arrivée d'Endrick à l'OL jusqu'à la fin de la saison|publisher=Olympique Lyonnais|date=23 December 2025|language=fr}}</ref> On 11 January 2026, he made his debut, scoring a goal in a 2–1 away win over [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in the [[2025–26 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Endrick-42-minutes-et-deja-buteur-pour-sa-premiere-avec-l-ol-en-coupe-de-france/1632829 |title=Endrick, 42 minutes et déjà buteur pour sa première avec l'OL en Coupe de France : son but en vidéo |publisher=L'Équipe |language=fr |date=11 January 2026 }}</ref> On 25 January, he scored his first goals in the league, a [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] in a 5–2 win over [[FC Metz|Metz]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=25 January 2026 |title=Real Madrid loanee Endrick nets hat trick in Lyon win |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/47727551/real-madrid-loanee-endrick-nets-hat-trick-lyon-win |access-date=26 January 2026 |work=[[ESPN]]}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Endrick seleção vs inglaterra.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Endrick with the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] in 2024]]

===Youth career===
On 18 March 2022, Endrick was called up to the [[Brazil national under-17 football team|Brazilian national under-17 team]] to compete in the 2022 edition of the [[Montaigu Tournament]] in France.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.terra.com.br/esportes/brasil/com-endrick-na-lista-tecnicos-da-base-convocam-selecao-brasileira-sub-17-para-torneios-internacionais,5e6f6cf27069882242681ce6f5d9eb34xe5143j8.html|title=Com Endrick na lista, técnicos da base convocam Seleção Brasileira sub-17 para torneios internacionais|trans-title=With Endrick on the list, base coaches call up the Brazilian under-17 team for international tournaments|website=[[Terra (company)|Terra]]|language=pt-br|date=18 March 2022|access-date=18 March 2022|archive-date=20 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220320215058/https://www.terra.com.br/esportes/brasil/com-endrick-na-lista-tecnicos-da-base-convocam-selecao-brasileira-sub-17-para-torneios-internacionais,5e6f6cf27069882242681ce6f5d9eb34xe5143j8.html|url-status=live}}</ref> With five goals in four matches, including one against Argentina in the final, Endrick finished as the top scorer and was named best player of the tournament, as Brazil won their first Montaigu Tournament title since 1984.<ref>{{cite web|last=Miller|first=Nick|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3258049/2022/10/28/watching-endrick-low-centre-of-gravity-deadly-finishing-and-pace-to-make-defenders-look-stupid/|title=Watching Endrick: Low centre of gravity, deadly finishing and pace to make defenders look stupid|work=[[The Athletic]]|date=28 October 2022|access-date=28 October 2022|archive-date=28 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221028111850/https://theathletic.com/3258049/2022/10/28/watching-endrick-low-centre-of-gravity-deadly-finishing-and-pace-to-make-defenders-look-stupid/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Endrick was initially included in [[Brazil national under-20 football team|Brazil's under-20 squad]] for the [[2023 South American U-20 Championship|2023 South American Youth Championship]] in Colombia. However, as his club Palmeiras elected not to release him, he would ultimately not be a part of Brazil's title-winning team; Palmeiras did not want Endrick to miss the start of their pre-season, which overlapped with the tournament's January and February timeframe.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/palmeiras/noticia/2022/12/27/palmeiras-comunica-cbf-que-nao-vai-liberar-endrick-e-giovani-para-selecao-sub-20.ghtml|title=Palmeiras comunica CBF que não vai liberar Endrick e Giovani para Seleção sub-20|trans-title=Palmeiras informs CBF that they will not release Endrick and Giovani for the U-20 national team|publisher=[[Globo Esporte]]|first=Emilio|last=Botta|date=27 December 2022|language=pt-br|access-date=19 October 2023|archive-date=11 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231111065330/https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/palmeiras/noticia/2022/12/27/palmeiras-comunica-cbf-que-nao-vai-liberar-endrick-e-giovani-para-selecao-sub-20.ghtml|url-status=live}}</ref>

Endrick was selected for the [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil national under-23 team]] in 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-22 |title=Can Real Madrid hope Endrick lead Brazil to the Olympics? |url=https://olympics.com/en/news/football-real-madrid-endrick-brazil-olympics |access-date=2024-01-24 |publisher=[[Olympics]] |archive-date=22 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240122173011/https://olympics.com/en/news/football-real-madrid-endrick-brazil-olympics |url-status=live }}</ref> The team failed to qualify for [[2024 Summer Olympics]] in Paris, France, with him scoring twice in seven matches in Olympic qualifying.<ref>{{Cite web |last=López |first=Juan Carlos Vera |date=2024-01-23 |title=Brazil defeats Bolivia 1-0 on day 2 of the U23 Pre-Olympic |url=https://www.vavel.com/en-us/soccer/2024/01/23/1169556-bolivia-vs-brasil-live-updates-score-updates-stream-info-lineups-and-how-to-watchu23-preolympic-match.html |access-date=2024-01-24 |website=[[VAVEL]] |archive-date=24 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240124034422/https://www.vavel.com/en-us/soccer/2024/01/23/1169556-bolivia-vs-brasil-live-updates-score-updates-stream-info-lineups-and-how-to-watchu23-preolympic-match.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Brazil fails to qualify for 2024 Olympics amid struggles in 2026 World Cup qualifying |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/brazil-fails-to-qualify-for-2024-olympics-amid-struggles-in-2026-world-cup-qualifying |access-date=2024-07-27 |website=FOX Sports |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Rampling |first=Ali |title=Brazil fail to qualify for Olympics following Argentina loss |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5269099/2024/02/12/brazil-argentina-2024-olympics-soccer/ |access-date=2024-07-27 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=12 February 2024 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

===Senior career===
Endrick was selected for the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] for the first time on 6 November 2023, to participate in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] and [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-06 |title=Fernando Diniz convoca Seleção Brasileira para jogos das Eliminatórias |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/fernando-diniz-convoca-selecao-brasileira-para-jogos-das-eliminatorias-1 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231106184551/https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/fernando-diniz-convoca-selecao-brasileira-para-jogos-das-eliminatorias-1 |archive-date=6 November 2023 |access-date=2023-11-06 |publisher=[[Confederação Brasileira de Futebol]] |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-06 |title=Brazil summons teenage sensation Endrick for World Cup qualifiers |url=https://apnews.com/article/brazil-argentina-endrick-world-cup-qualifying-372c04347e5bdbddf4840d339b57499d |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231107041723/https://apnews.com/article/brazil-argentina-endrick-world-cup-qualifying-372c04347e5bdbddf4840d339b57499d |archive-date=7 November 2023 |access-date=2023-11-07 |publisher=[[AP News]] |language=en}}</ref> He became the youngest male player to secure a senior call-up since [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]] in 1994.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-06 |title=Endrick earns first Brazil call-up |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/fernando-diniz-names-endrick-brazil-squad-world-cup-2026-qualifiers-qualifying |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231106184551/https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/fernando-diniz-names-endrick-brazil-squad-world-cup-2026-qualifiers-qualifying |archive-date=6 November 2023 |access-date=2023-11-06 |publisher=[[FIFA]]}}</ref> On his debut against Colombia, he became the fourth all-time youngest player, and youngest in 57 years, to make his debut for Brazil.<ref>{{cite web |title=Madrid's Endrick becomes fourth youngest player to make Brazil debut |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/madrid-s-endrick-becomes-fourth-youngest-player-to-make-brazil-debut-1290050 |website=BeSoccer |access-date=8 December 2023 |language=en |date=17 November 2023 |archive-date=8 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208101623/https://www.besoccer.com/new/madrid-s-endrick-becomes-fourth-youngest-player-to-make-brazil-debut-1290050 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=South America qualifiers: Brazil falls to Colombia in Endrick |url=https://www.sambafoot.com/brazilian-national-team/south-america-qualifiers-brazil-falls-to-colombia-in-endricks-debut |website=Sambafoot EN |access-date=8 December 2023 |date=17 November 2023 |archive-date=8 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208101623/https://www.sambafoot.com/brazilian-national-team/south-america-qualifiers-brazil-falls-to-colombia-in-endricks-debut |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Samson |first1=Ero |title=Real Madrid forward Endrick makes history with debut against Colombia |url=https://sportsbrief.com/football/53172-real-madrids-endrick-achieves-milestone-following-debut-in-brazils-clash-against-colombia/ |website=Sports Brief |access-date=8 December 2023 |language=en |date=19 November 2023 |archive-date=8 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208101623/https://sportsbrief.com/football/53172-real-madrids-endrick-achieves-milestone-following-debut-in-brazils-clash-against-colombia/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His side fell to a 2–1 defeat at the [[Estadio Metropolitano Roberto Meléndez]] as Colombia achieved their first qualifier victory over Brazil in their history.<ref>{{cite web |title=Diaz and Nunez sparkle as Colombia and Uruguay slay giants |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/conmebol-south-american-qualifying-round-five-review-world-cup-2026 |publisher=FIFA |access-date=8 December 2023 |date=17 November 2023 |archive-date=8 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231208101623/https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/conmebol-south-american-qualifying-round-five-review-world-cup-2026 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Endrick scored his first goal for Brazil in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[England national football team|England]] at [[Wembley Stadium]] on 23 March 2024, making him the youngest player to score for club or country at the ground.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=2024-03-23 |title=Teenager Endrick fires Brazil to win over England |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68647860 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240429124545/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68647860 |archive-date=2024-04-29 |access-date=2024-03-23 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> He scored his second goal for his nation three days later in a 3–3 draw to [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Sullivan |first1=Joseph |date=27 March 2024 |title=Spain 3–3 Brazil, Yamine Lamal And Endrick Star In Classic Battle |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/josephosullivan/2024/03/27/spain-3-3-brazil-yamine-lamal-and-endrick-star-in-classic-battle/ |access-date=10 June 2024 |work=[[Forbes]] |language=en}}</ref> On 10 May, he was called up for Brazil to participate in the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-05-10 |title=Dorival Júnior anuncia convocados para a Copa América |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/dorival-junior-anuncia-jogadores-para-a-disputa-da-copa-america |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240516123444/https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/dorival-junior-anuncia-jogadores-para-a-disputa-da-copa-america |archive-date=2024-05-16 |access-date=2024-05-10 |publisher=Confederação Brasileira de Futebol |language=pt-BR}}</ref> After three sub appearances in the [[2024 Copa América Group D|group stage]], he made his first start for Brazil, replacing [[Vinícius Júnior]] who was suspended, in a [[2024 Copa América knockout stage|quarter-final]] defeat to [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Burrows |first1=Ben |last2=Harris |first2=Thom |last3=Lang |first3=Jack |date=6 July 2024 |title=Endrick to make first Brazil start in Uruguay quarterfinal |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5619097/2024/07/05/endrick-starts-brazil-team-news/ |access-date=9 July 2024 |work=The New York Times |language=en}}</ref> Endrick completed one pass during the match, from kick-off, as his side lost 4–2 in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mewis |first1=Joe |title=Brazil starlet Endrick's barely believable stat in Copa America exit to Uruguay |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/brazil-starlet-endricks-barely-believable-stat-in-copa-america-exit-to-uruguay |website=fourfourtwo.com |access-date=9 July 2024 |language=en |date=8 July 2024}}</ref> On 18 May 2026, Endrick was named to Brazil's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/a/carlo-ancelotti-convoca-os-26-jogadores-que-vao-tentar-o-hexa-na-copa-do-mundo |title=Carlo Ancelotti convoca os 26 jogadores que vão tentar o hexa na Copa do Mundo |trans-title=Carlo Ancelotti names the 26 players who will attempt to win the sixth World Cup title |publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation]] |date=May 18, 2026 |access-date=May 19, 2026 |language=pt |url-status=live |archive-date=May 19, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260519061627/https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/a/carlo-ancelotti-convoca-os-26-jogadores-que-vao-tentar-o-hexa-na-copa-do-mundo}}</ref>

==Personal life==
[[File: Jude Bellingham and Endrick in 2024.jpg|thumb|upright|Endrick with his teammate [[Jude Bellingham]] during the [[EA Sports FC 25]] launch event in September 2024]]

After scoring the winning goal for Brazil over England on 23 March 2024,<ref name=":0" /> Endrick revealed that he idolised the late English forward [[Bobby Charlton]]. Brazil and Real Madrid forward [[Rodrygo]] revealed on 8 September 2024 that his teammates began calling Endrick "Bobby" as a form of banter after he revealed his admiration for Charlton.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-09 |title=Endrick's surprising tribute to Charlton has Brazilians calling him 'Bobby' |url=https://apnews.com/article/endrick-brazil-bobby-51870948c6be54750a1b5c46aed69369 |access-date=2024-09-17 |website=AP News |language=en}}</ref>

In September 2024, Endrick married his girlfriend, Gabriely Miranda.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 September 2024 |title=Endrick gets married |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/realmadrid-2024-09-16-endrick-gets-married/ |access-date=16 September 2024 |website=Tribuna.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Botija |first1=Julio |last2=Nelson |first2=David |date=2024-09-16 |title=Real Madrid player gets married... at 18! |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/real-madrid-player-gets-married-at-18-n/ |access-date=2024-09-18 |publisher=[[AS USA]] |language=en-us}}</ref>

In November 2024, he became a [[Baptist Christian]] and was baptized at [[Lagoinha Baptist Church]] in [[Madrid]].<ref>Geoffrey Leplang, [https://www.evangeliques.info/2024/11/07/le-footballeur-endrick-baptise-dans-une-eglise-evangelique-a-madrid/ Le footballeur Endrick baptisé dans une Église évangélique à Madrid], evangeliques.info, Switzerland, November 7, 2024</ref>

==Style of play==
A left-footed forward with a good shot, Endrick is considered one of Brazil's best football prospects,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/br/not%C3%ADcias/fifa-cita-idolos-do-palmeiras-e-destaca-o-gol-de-bicicleta/bltb44a0a2a48c6a9b8 |title=Fifa cita ídolos do Palmeiras e destaca o gol de bicicleta de Endrick na Copinha |website=[[Goal.com]] |date=21 January 2022 |language=pt |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=6 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006233334/https://www.goal.com/br/not%C3%ADcias/fifa-cita-idolos-do-palmeiras-e-destaca-o-gol-de-bicicleta/bltb44a0a2a48c6a9b8 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/paises/brasil/detalhe/nas-bocas-do-mundo-saiba-quem-e-endrick-o-jogador-do-palmeiras-que-ja-e-cobicado-pelo-barca |title=Nas bocas do mundo: Saiba quem é Endrick, o jogador do Palmeiras que já é cobiçado pelo Barça |website=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record.pt]] |date=21 January 2022 |language=pt |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=6 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006233340/https://www.record.pt/internacional/paises/brasil/detalhe/nas-bocas-do-mundo-saiba-quem-e-endrick-o-jogador-do-palmeiras-que-ja-e-cobicado-pelo-barca |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://footballtalentscout.net/2022/01/10/endrick/ |title=Endrick |website=Football Talents Scout |date=10 January 2022 |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=6 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006233334/https://footballtalentscout.net/2022/01/10/endrick/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and has drawn comparisons with legendary Brazilian strikers [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], [[Pelé]], and [[Romário]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2022/01/10/lavieri-endrick-esta-mais-para-ronaldo-ou-romario-do-que-para-vini-jr.htm |title=Lavieri: 'Endrick está mais para Ronaldo ou Romário do que para Vini Jr' |website=[[Universo Online]] |date=10 January 2022 |language=pt-br |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=6 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006233332/https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2022/01/10/lavieri-endrick-esta-mais-para-ronaldo-ou-romario-do-que-para-vini-jr.htm |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.football.london/chelsea-fc/news/chelsea-manchester-united-next-ronaldo-22837808 |title=Chelsea join Manchester United, Barcelona and Real Madrid in race to sign 'next Ronaldo' |website=Football.London |date=22 January 2022 |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-date=6 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006233335/https://www.football.london/chelsea-fc/news/chelsea-manchester-united-next-ronaldo-22837808 |url-status=live }}</ref> Endrick has rejected comparisons of his ability to Brazilian legends and particularly towards Pelé.<ref>{{cite web |date=5 April 2023 |title=Madrid-bound Endrick: Don't compare me to Pele |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37637747/compare-pele |access-date=1 June 2023 |publisher=ESPN |archive-date=1 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230601212531/https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37637747/compare-pele |url-status=live }}</ref> When asked to describe his style of play, Endrick said, "I'll always fight. I'll be persistent and try until the last minute I'm in the game. I never give up, I pressure defenders, I run more than anyone else on the pitch."<ref>{{cite web |title=Is this the next Brazilian Wonderkid? |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=na4XkAFyH-o |website=YouTube |author=Tifo Football |date=9 May 2022 |access-date=9 May 2022 |archive-date=9 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220509084836/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=na4XkAFyH-o |url-status=live }}</ref> His father has stated that the footballer has been inspired by Portuguese forward [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].<ref>{{cite web |date=20 January 2022 |title=Pai de Endrick revela inspiração do filho em Cristiano Ronaldo: 'Quer ser igual' |url=https://nossopalestra.com.br/palmeiras/noticias/pai-de-endrick-revela-inspiracao-do-filho-em-cristiano-ronaldo-quer-ser-igual/ |website=Nosso Palestra |language=pt-br |access-date=26 January 2022 |archive-date=6 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006233334/https://nossopalestra.com.br/palmeiras/noticias/pai-de-endrick-revela-inspiracao-do-filho-em-cristiano-ronaldo-quer-ser-igual/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

